South Africa has recorded nine more deaths from COVID-19 pushing the death toll from the virus to 247.  There are  13 524 confirmed cases of the virus according to the Health Department. The number of recoveries is at 6 083 while over 420 000 tests have been conducted thus far.   Below is a graph on latest COVID-19 statistics:  SA COVID-19 CASES       Total cases    Recovered    Deaths    Active cases 13 524  7 194   * as at 15 May 2020 6 083  247     TOTAL TESTS CONDUCTED 421 555  @SABCNEWS sabcnews.com |  SABC News channel | SABC Radio news (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document)); Coronavirus on the rise in Correctional Services The Department of Correctional Services (DCS) on Friday announced 14 new COVID-19 cases, following seven  officials and four inmates from the Western Cape and two officials from the Eastern Cape testing positive. The  Northern Cape has registered one additional case. The total number of cases is now at 378, whilst the number of recoveries remain at 92. Below is  breakdown of the numbers:  COVID-19 CASES IN SOUTH AFRICAN PRISONS WESTERN CAPE LIMPOPO GAUTENG EASTERN CAPE 23 0 9 181 99 2 6 1 54 PRISONERS OFFICIALS Source: The Department of Correctional Services AS AT  15 MAY 2020 59 30 1 1 1 RECOVERIES CONFIRMED CASES | 378 DEATHS 2 2 HEAD OFFICE KZN NORTHERN CAPE 0 0 2 1 0 0 sabcnews.com |  SABC News channel | SABC Radio news @SABCNEWS @SABCNEWS sabcnews.com |  SABC News channel | SABC Radio news (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document));